<h2>Introduction</h2>
sedExnerFoam is an OpenFOAM solver in development aiming at the numerical study of various sediment transport and morphodynamics problems.

This manual is written as the documentation of the open-source solver sedExnerFoam, it includes the installation procedure and a description of the model input/output files. 

The sedExnerFoam solver should be referenced using the GMD paper :

Renaud, M., Bertrand, O., Bonamy, C., and Chauchat, J. (2026) sedExnerFoam 2412: A 3D Exner-based sediment transport and morphodynamics model, Geosci. Model Dev., review in progress, https://doi.org/10.5194/egusphere-2025-2375.

If you are using a sedExnerFoam version without modification, you should also refer to the Zenodo DOI of the version, current version is https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.15535485



The documentation is divided into two parts, the first one is the user manual:
<ul>
<li>Section \ref install explains how to download, compile and install sedExnerFoam.
<li>Section \ref howtodocker provides a survival guide on how to use SedExnerFoam docker (in progress).
<li>Section \ref governingEq describes sedExnerFoam governing equations (in progress). 
<li>Section \ref tutorials_laminar describes the laminar flow tutorials provided with sedExnerFoam sources including postprocessing using a python toolbox also provided with the source and the expected results.
<li>Section \ref inputs describes the input parameters for SedFoam.
<li>Section \ref howtogit provides a survival guide on how to use git to use/develop sedExnerFoam.
<li>Section \ref faq provides answers to typical Frequently Asked Questions about sedExnerFoam 
</ul>


The second part provides informations for developers.

